data.description: (** this property is eligible for several very attractive grants that require no pay back. Up to 17,500. These grants are NOT just for 1st time Buyers. ) Nestled in the historic and Civic-Minded Triangle Neighborhood, 2013 Baynard Blvd embodies the timeless charm of classic architecture coupled with today’s modern comforts. This captivating residence welcomes you with its stately façade adorned with a beautiful wrap around porch and lush greenery, exuding a sense of warmth and sophistication. Upon entry, you are greeted by an inviting spacious foyer features a wood burning fireplace, Crown Molding, & the Classic staircase with all its period grace. This foyer leads seamlessly into the elegant living spaces. The spacious living room boasts large windows with 14” deep windowsills, allowing natural light to cascade in, illuminating the rich oak hardwood floors.  The gourmet kitchen is a culinary enthusiast's dream, featuring Quartz Countertops, Custom Cabinetry, Island with a Gas Range, Under Counter Lighting, deep sink, high-end Stainless-Steel Appliances recessed lighting. The original butler stairway takes you to the 2nd floor hallway. And whether hosting intimate gatherings or grand affairs, the adjacent Formal Dining Room provides a gracious setting for memorable meals and lively conversations with original pocket doors and a handsome, coffered beam ceiling. There’s Butler’s pantry with period cabinetry, with a privately located Powder Room as well.  As you head up the stairs, you will be sure to note the unique 12’ x 4” Victorian window. Oh, the wonderful sunshine that comes through!   On the 2nd floor you will fine 4 graciously sized bedrooms with Hardwood flooring, Period Doors/Hardware & Moldings. Off the right bedroom is a fantastic, enclosed Sleeping Porch which overlooks the back yard. The recently renovated Hall Bathroom is adorned with hexagon white tile flooring & white fixtures including a deep soaking tub/shower.   The 3rd floor has 3 more sizable bedrooms with interesting roof lines (but not comprised head room),  a spacious full bath with a sleigh soaking tub, plus an interesting storage room with pulldown stairs to the attic space for additional storage.   Step outside to discover an enchanting outdoor oasis, where manicured gardens and a serene patio create an ideal setting for al fresco dining or leisurely relaxation. The beautiful backyard offers ample space for outdoor activities & entertainment, perfect for enjoying warm summer days & cool evenings under the stars. Conveniently located near local amenities, parks, and renowned dining destinations, 2013 Baynard Blvd presents an unparalleled opportunity to experience the best of Wilmington living. With its timeless elegance, modern amenities, and prime location, this residence is truly a place to call home. BTW, this property is elgible for several grants with up to approx $17,500 k which does not need to be paid back!
